column5: message
Add a link to the Wiki in the README
Fix a bug where concurrent call argument would not properly get passed kwargs
Increment version number, includes bug fixes for synchronized decorator and KeyboardInterrupt handling
Fix operations getting called multiple times, add a test
Call async_result.get with a timeout so that KeyboardInterrupts are handled better
Fixed a bug where tainted returns caused visit_Return to return [waits, [more_waits, node]] instead of [waits, node]

Increment version number

Includes deferred function calls, and refactors/simplifications to the AST parsing of @synchronized functions
Fix a bug where a waits would not be inserted inside synchronized functions, also fix a test to catch this problem

Merge pull request #44 from alex-sherman/function_call

Function call
Increment version number, fix a test case
Fix a bug where waits wouldn't get inserted for referenced variables
Fix a compatibility issue with Python 3 AST changes to Lambdas
Fix a bug where invalid @concurrent uses weren't caught
Improve synchronized to throw useful errors in unsupported use cases
Initial support for deferred function calls
Fixed a bug where assignments wouldn't get cleared after a synchronization event
Version 0.4.1
Fixed a bug with indentation and added an error message when using these decorators on class methods
Added a test for arguments with subscripts/indexes
Changed kwarg test to verify that proxying occurs, and fixed a bug causing it to not, also support kwargs in Python3
Version 0.4
Added concurrent.threaded and wrapped the return value of apply_async to be more useful without @synchronized

Added support for custom concurrency

Initial design for custom concurrency which has proven to support
ThreadPool and theoretically should support other concurrency
mechanisms.
Fixed a bug with expressions with bodies containing single elements

Improve handling of argument reference detection

Argument references now look for the top level name, traversing
subscripts and attributes. Concurrent function calls now support
**kwargs arguments as well.
Add a limitations section to README
Added simple loop example
Make setup.py executable
Change version to 0.3
Switch to MIT license

Support Python 3.5

Added initial support for Python 3.5, working with the climate model
example but untested for nbody and hash_test.

Fix compatibility issues, improved AST parsing

Pool now gets its arguments passed from the concurrent decorator.
Removed the default number of processes getting set to 3. Removed global
variable proxying, it caused some issues with aliased names. AST parsing
now handles some more cases, still will probably miss more complicated
references.

Added a license
Typos.

Merge pull request #3 from benmoran56/master

Some Python 2/3 dual compatibility fixes.
Version 0.2
Fix a typo in README
Better handling of @synchronized refactoring, included a README
Initial support for reference detection and synchronization
Initial implementation of @synchronized
Included a timing analysis test
Performance improvements from switch to Pool, greatly simplified the code base
Global variable proxying
Added test code for free variables

Added free variable detection and now automatically proxy them instead of the "globals" argument.

function locals are currently placed into the "self.free_names" set as well as true free variables because if the module scope doesn't have globals with those names it just skips them. This could be changed but it doesn't impact functionality (afaik)
Fixed a bug when processing arguments of the concurrenct decorator
Added a setup.py and allow some parameters to the concurrent decorator
Added an nbody example and got globals working
Initial commit with slightly working decorator
Initial commit
